virulency.d:
n. The quality or state of being virulent or venomous;
   poisonousness; malignancy.
n. Extreme bitterness or malignity of disposition.

vitrescence.d:
n. The quality or state of being vitreous; glassiness, or
   the quality of being vitrescent; capability of conversion into glass;
   susceptibility of being formed into glass.
